{"version":"2.1.0","runs":[{"invocations":[{"executionSuccessful":true,"toolExecutionNotifications":[{"descriptor":{"id":"Syntax error"},"level":"warning","message":{"text":"Syntax error at line /opt/chronicle/chronicle-server/src/main/kotlin/com/openlattice/chronicle/configuration/RateLimitFilter.kt:289:\n `annotation.` was unexpected"}}]}],"results":[],"tool":{"driver":{"name":"Semgrep OSS","rules":[{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: multiple adjacent unbounded quantifiers detected. Patterns like .*.*,  .+.+, or \\w+\\d+ cause catastrophic backtracking because the regex engine tries exponentially many ways to split the input between the quantified expressions. Use atomic groups, possessive quantifiers, or refactor to eliminate ambiguous repetition."},"help":{"markdown":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: multiple adjacent unbounded quantifiers detected. Patterns like .*.*,  .+.+, or \\w+\\d+ cause catastrophic backtracking because the regex engine tries exponentially many ways to split the input between the quantified expressions. Use atomic groups, possessive quantifiers, or refactor to eliminate ambiguous repetition.","text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: multiple adjacent unbounded quantifiers detected. Patterns like .*.*,  .+.+, or \\w+\\d+ cause catastrophic backtracking because the regex engine tries exponentially many ways to split the input between the quantified expressions. Use atomic groups, possessive quantifiers, or refactor to eliminate ambiguous repetition."},"id":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-catastrophic-backtracking","name":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-catastrophic-backtracking","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-1333","OWASP-A06:2021","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Semgrep Finding: tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-catastrophic-backtracking"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: nested quantifiers detected in regex pattern. Patterns like (a+)+, (a*)*, (a+)*, or (a*)+ cause exponential backtracking on non-matching input, leading to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS). Refactor the regex to avoid nesting quantifiers inside quantified groups."},"help":{"markdown":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: nested quantifiers detected in regex pattern. Patterns like (a+)+, (a*)*, (a+)*, or (a*)+ cause exponential backtracking on non-matching input, leading to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS). Refactor the regex to avoid nesting quantifiers inside quantified groups.","text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: nested quantifiers detected in regex pattern. Patterns like (a+)+, (a*)*, (a+)*, or (a*)+ cause exponential backtracking on non-matching input, leading to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS). Refactor the regex to avoid nesting quantifiers inside quantified groups."},"id":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-nested-quantifier","name":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-nested-quantifier","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-1333","OWASP-A06:2021","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Semgrep Finding: tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-nested-quantifier"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: overlapping alternation inside a quantified group. Patterns like (a|a)+, (\\w|\\d)+, or (.*|.+)+ contain alternation branches that can match the same input, causing exponential backtracking on non-matching input. Ensure alternation branches are mutually exclusive or refactor to avoid ambiguity."},"help":{"markdown":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: overlapping alternation inside a quantified group. Patterns like (a|a)+, (\\w|\\d)+, or (.*|.+)+ contain alternation branches that can match the same input, causing exponential backtracking on non-matching input. Ensure alternation branches are mutually exclusive or refactor to avoid ambiguity.","text":"Potential ReDoS vulnerability: overlapping alternation inside a quantified group. Patterns like (a|a)+, (\\w|\\d)+, or (.*|.+)+ contain alternation branches that can match the same input, causing exponential backtracking on non-matching input. Ensure alternation branches are mutually exclusive or refactor to avoid ambiguity."},"id":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-overlapping-alternation","name":"tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-overlapping-alternation","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-1333","OWASP-A06:2021","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Semgrep Finding: tests.security.rules.chronicle-redos-overlapping-alternation"}}],"semanticVersion":"1.155.0"}}}],"$schema":"https://docs.oasis-open.org/sarif/sarif/v2.1.0/os/schemas/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json"}